Class YRCCellModifier2

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yantra.yfc.rcp.YRCBaseCellModifier
      • com.yantra.yfc.rcp.IYRCCellModifier
        • com.yantra.yfc.rcp.YRCCellModifier2

  • public abstract class YRCCellModifier2
extends IYRCCellModifier
    Utility class extending the IYRCCellModifier with default behavior.

    Applications should use this class and implement required methods. It is recommended to use this class for handling editable cells as this provides the ability to set the custom error messages (if any).

    See Also:
    validateModifiedValue(String, String, Element)

      • validateModifiedValue

        protected abstract YRCValidationResponse validateModifiedValue(java.lang.String property,
                                                               java.lang.String value,
                                                               org.w3c.dom.Element element)
        This method is used to check if the vaue modified by the user is correct. If it is OK to modify the current value, IYRCCellModifier.getModifiedValue(String, String, Element) is called and the entered value is formatted according to its data type. In rest of the cases no further processing is done. In case of error, the cell is set in error. If the field is in error, return the validation response with proper error message. This error message is displayed when required to do so.
        Parameters:
        property - The property associated with the current table column.
        value - The modified value in the cell.
        element - The element corresponding to the current row.
        Returns:
        The validation response indicating the response type.
        See Also:
        YRCValidationResponse
